About Us:

At Elexon Mining, we're not just building in-ground wireless monitoring solutions; we're empowering the future of mining.  We are passionate about creating the world's most advanced technology, enabling mines globally to operate safer, smarter, and more efficiently. From our base in Brisbane, Australia, we design and manufacture the innovative CaveTracker and Geo4Sight systems that are transforming the industry.

Since 2006, our commitment to innovation and strong partnerships with miners, geotechnical engineers, geologists, and researchers has propelled us to global leadership.  Our systems deliver critical insights, providing the data intelligence mines need to make informed decisions.  We're driven by a collaborative spirit and a relentless pursuit of doing it better.

Join us at the forefront of mining technology, where your contributions will shape the future of the industry.

About the Role:

The Production Engineer is responsible for the design, development, implementation & optimisation of Production Processes, Systems, Equipment & Tools. This broad Engineering roll will involve a range of manufacturing-focused activities in arenas such as:

PRODUCT DESIGN SUPPORT

Providing engineering expertise & support for products that are or have transitioned to production. This will involve:

o   providing manufacturing methods guidance to Design Engineers, and conducting ‘Design For Manufacture & Assembly’ (DFMA) Reviews;

o   planning for the transition of new product designs into Production;


PRODUCTION PROCESS DEVELOPMENT

Providing design, implementation & optimisation of Production Processes. This will involve:

o   validating new products, processes & equipment prior to Production Release;

o   assisting in the review and optimisation of current process capabilities & capacities;

o   designing & arranging for the fabrication/installation of new assembly benches, jigs, fixtures & custom-tools;

o   creating and updating work & maintenance instructions;


PLANT & EQUIPMENT MAINTENANCE

Providing oversight & implementation of production plant & equipment maintenance.

PRODUCTION STAFF EQUIPPING & TRAINING

From time-to-time, providing appropriate levels of training to Production staff.




ESSENTIAL

·         Bachelor (or higher) of Engineering Degree in electrical, electronic, industrial, process, or significant equivalent technical experience in lieu of formal qualifications.

·         At least 3 years hands-on experience within an electronics manufacturing environment.

·         Experience in SMD

·         Experience in several different phases of the product development or product manufacturing lifecycles.

·         Positive, cooperative and supportive attitude.

·         High degree of self-motivation.

·         Excellent verbal and written communication skills.

·         A willingness to work to written procedures;

·         The ability to determine and negotiate priorities in a dynamic work environment;

·         Experience in manufacturing complex, electronic products;

·         Experience maintaining production machinery, including programming robotic machines;

·         Experience in developing automated test jigs;

·         Experienced in software development for supporting test automation and integration;

·         Prior training and practical experience in LEAN &/or 6-Sigma programs;

·         Prior training and practical experience in Quality Systems, AS9001 implementation, TQM, JIT, IPC Soldering & Inspection, projects management.

·         The right to work in Australia, or by holding the appropriate Australian Visa to allow employment.
